# Approach
- The last "1" will take the longest time to travel to its destination in the string, which is the number of "0"s infront. 
- The special case is when "1" is right next to another "1", which will add one more step for the second 1 to move to the right.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)

- Space complexity: O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution:
    def secondsToRemoveOccurrences(self, s: str) -> int:
        n = len(s)
        count, res = 0, 0

        for i in range(n):
            if (s[i] == '0'):
                count += 1
            else:
                if count > 0:
                    res = max(res+1, count)

        return res
```

