# Approach
1. While there are replaces to be made, traverse the char[] chars of String from 0 to n and replace all 01 with 10. 
After each loop, if changes have been made, increment the steps, break otherwise.
2. Return the number of steps.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(n * n - worst-case)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:$$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int secondsToRemoveOccurrences(String s) {
        char[] chrs = s.toCharArray();
        boolean swapped = true;
        int steps = 0;
        while(swapped) {
            swapped = false;
            for (int i = 0; i < s.length() - 1; i++) {       
                if (chrs[i] == '0' && chrs[i+1] == '1') {
                    chrs[i] = '1';
                    chrs[i+1] = '0';
                    i++;
                    swapped = true;
                }
            }
            if(swapped) {
                steps++;
            }
        }
        return steps;
    }
}
```

