# Intuition
Took me a while and a few iterations to get here. If current 1 encounters or gets blocked the previous 1, then the answer is one more than the previous one. Whether or not current 1 encounters a previous 1 depends on the number of 0s before it.

# Approach
Simple for loop that keeps track of num0s and previous ans to compute the current answer.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int secondsToRemoveOccurrences(string s) {
        int num0s = 0, ans = 0;
        for (char ch : s) {
            if (ch == '0') {
                num0s++;
                continue;
            }
            // ignore the 1s if there are no 0s.
            if (num0s == 0) continue;
            ans = max(ans + 1, num0s);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
