solutions.content:
- After completely swapping all the '01' to '10', at the end we will get a sorted string in such a way that all the 1's will come before all the 0's. Eg. if a string is "10111000" it will become "11110000" at the end.
- So we will make a temporary string equal to the string we will obtain at the end and run a loop until our original string becomes equal to that string.
- Then in each iteration of while loop we will maintain the indices of the 0's who have 1 as the next element and swap them all at once and increment the time needed by 1.
- Doing so will give us the answer. 
```
class Solution {
public:
    int secondsToRemoveOccurrences(string s) {
        int ans = 0;
        string temp = s;
        sort(temp.begin(),temp.end());
        reverse(temp.begin(),temp.end());
        while(s!=temp){
            vector<int> v;
            for(int i = 0;i<s.length()-1;i++){
                if(s[i] == '0' && s[i+1] == '1'){
                    v.push_back(i);
                }
            }
            for(int i = 0;i<v.size();i++){
                swap(s[v[i]],s[v[i]+1]);
            }
            ans++;
        }
         return ans;
    }
};
```

