**INTUITION :**
We have to increase/decrease every character by one if lying in the given range.

# **First Approach (NAIVE TLE) :**
The naive approach would be for evey shift[i] run a loop from shift[i][0] to shift[i][1] and increment or decrement depending upon shift[i][2].
This is a possible solution but give TLE as per the given constraints.

**CODE** *(TLE)*
```
char shiftBack(char ch)  //Shift Forword
    {
        if(ch=='a')
            return 'z';
        return char(int(ch) - 1);
    }

    char shiftFor(char ch)
    {
        if(ch=='z')
            return 'a';
        return char(int(ch) + 1);
    }

    string shiftingLetters(string s, vector<vector<int>>& shifts) {
        for(auto ele:shifts)
        {
            int from = ele[0];
            int to = ele[1];
            int dir = ele[2];
            if(dir==0)
            {
                for(int i=from;i<=to;i++)
                {
                    s[i]=shiftBack(s[i]);
                }
            }
            else
            {
                for(int i=from;i<=to;i++)
                {
                    s[i]=shiftFor(s[i]);
                }
            }
        }
        return s;
    }
```

# **Second Approach (Accepted Sol.)**

Here in this Approach we are going to use is ***PREFIX SUM***.
create a vector of integers (say v) assigh 0 to it,
For every shift   
*if shift[i][0] is 1*:
* 	Increase v[shift[i][0]] by 1 and if shift[i][0]+1 is within the range then decrese v[shift[i][0]+1] by 1

if shift[i][0] is 0:
* 	decrease v[shift[i][0]] by 1 and if shift[i][0]+1 is within the range then increase v[shift[i][0]+1] by 1

**Then calculate prefix sum in a differnet array (say psum) of v and for every index increment the character at that index by psum[i].**

**CODE**(Accepted Sol.)
```
string shiftingLetters(string s, vector<vector<int>>& shifts) {
        vector<int>v(s.length(),0);

        for(auto ele:shifts)
        {
            int from = ele[0];
            int to = ele[1];
            int dir = ele[2];
            if(dir==0)
            {
                v[from]--;
                if(to+1<v.size())
                {
                    v[to+1]++;
                }
            }
            else
            {
                v[from]++;
                if(to+1<v.size())
                {
                    v[to+1]--;
                }
            }
        }
        vector<int>psum(v.size(),0);
        psum[0]=v[0];
        for(int i=1;i<v.size();i++)
        {
            psum[i]=v[i]+psum[i-1];
        }

        for(int i=0;i<psum.size();i++)
        {
            char res;
            int ele = psum[i];
            int n=s[i];
            ele=ele%26;
            if(ele>=0)
            {
                res = char( (n%97 + ele)%26 + 97);
            }
            else
            {
                ele = 26-abs(ele);
                res = char( (n%97 + ele)%26 + 97);
            }
            s[i]=res;
        }
        return s;
    }
```

***TC: O(N)
SC: O(N)***

