# Intuition
As problem is related to segments, first thought was to use segment tree. But we have to increment each character, complexity will be n^2 to update segment tree. Then prefix sum will work as shown in approach below.

# Approach 
For example consider string of length 10.
If we have to update string as [2,5,1].
What we can do here is, we can increment each character from 2nd position till last. But to reduce updation after 5 at position we will derement it by 1;


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string shiftingLetters(string s, vector<vector<int>>& sf) {
        int n = s.size();
        vector<int>pf(n+1,0);
        for(int i=0;i<sf.size();i++){
            if(sf[i][2]==0){
                pf[sf[i][0]] -= 1;
                pf[sf[i][1]+1] += 1;
            }else{
                pf[sf[i][0]] += 1;
                pf[sf[i][1]+1] -= 1;
            }
        }

        int cur = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){

            cur += pf[i];

            cur %= 26;

            if(cur<0)
                cur += 26;

            int b =  s[i]+cur;

            if(b>122)
                b = b-26;

            s[i] = b;
        }
        return s;
    }
};
```

