**APPROACH is little bit tricky try to dry run this code , you will get the idea behind it**

first i used the ,priority Queue that will store the interval data
i.e., start index, end index, and sum of interval 
and sort them on the base of decreasing sum,

TreeSet, that will store the partitions , means queries value

Then i do prefic evaluation, means 
suppose query type is 1, 
then i do arr[st]++ and arr[en+1]--;
where st and en is the starting and ending index of query 

**IMPORTANT PART BEGIN FROM HERE** 

for every query i will , check the upper bound and lower bound ,
and add in my prioriy queue to 2 range
1st lowerbound to current query value
2nd current query value to upperbound 
same like the i split the query

then i run the while loop until i get the valid range(partition)
means range ,in which there is no parition between them

```
public long[] maximumSegmentSum(int[] nums, int[] quer) {       
        int n=nums.length;
        PriorityQueue<long []> pq=new PriorityQueue<>((long a[],long b[])->(a[2]<=b[2])?1:-1);  
        TreeSet<Integer> set=new TreeSet<>();
        long arr[]=new long[n],ans[]=new long[n];
        set.add(-1);
        set.add(n);
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            arr[i]=nums[i];
            if(i!=0) arr[i]+=arr[i-1];
        }
        pq.add(new long[]{0,n-1,arr[n-1]});
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            int num=quer[i];
            set.add(quer[i]);
            int a=set.lower(num), b=set.higher(num);
            if((a+1)<num){
                pq.add(new long[]{(long)a+1,(long)num-1,arr[num-1]-(long)((a==-1)?0:arr[a])});
            }
            if((num+1)<b){
                pq.add(new long[]{(long)num+1,(long)b-1,arr[b-1]-arr[num]});
            } 
            while(!pq.isEmpty()){
                long ab[]=pq.peek();
                int s=(int) ab[0],e=(int) ab[1];

                if(set.higher(s-1)>e){
                    ans[i]=pq.peek()[2];
                    break;
                }
                else pq.remove();
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
```

