solutions.content:
**Approach -**

Step 1 - Make a prefix sum array for getting the sum in O(1) (Constant time)
Step 2 - Declare a set of pair for storing all segments and a multiset for storing the sum of all segments
Step 3 - Insert starting segment i.e. {0,n-1} and starting sum i.e. sum of all elements in set and multiset respectively
Step 4 - traverse removeQueries array from 0 to n-2 ( last maximum sum is always 0 so no need to traverse till n-1)
	i)  Find that segment in a set of segments in which removeQueries[i] present.
	ii) Remove that segment and sum elements of that segment
	iii) Insert a new segment in the set which is come after breaking the previous segment
	iv) Find the sum of new segments and add them to multiset
	v) Find max sum in multiset and store in the answer

Q - > Why we used multiset?

Ans -> Let's understand using one example 

**One Example -** 

Arr - [1,2,3,4,5] , Remove - [3,0,4,2,1]

prefixSum ->  [1,3,6,10,15]
Set - > {{0,4}}
Multiset -> {15}

For -> Remove[0]
Set -> {{0,2},{4,4}}
Multiset -> {5,6}
Ans -> {6}

For -> Remove[1]
Set -> {{1,2},{4,4}}
Multiset -> {5,5}       -> **Here, if we use a set then we can not store multiple value of the same type**
Ans -> {6,5}

For -> Remove[2]
Set -> {{1,2}}
Multiset -> {5}
Ans -> {6,5,5}

For -> Remove[3]
Set -> {{1,1}}
Multiset -> {2}
Ans -> {6,5,5,2}

For -> Remove[4]
Set -> {}
Multiset -> {}
Ans -> {6,5,5,2,0}

**Output -> {6,5,5,2,0}**


