It was a great learning experience solving this challenge. Prefix sums, C++ Multiset, Upper Bound were the concepts used.
My thought process from brute to optimal below :
In case you prefer video solution, please refer :https://youtu.be/lZht4j2Ux-c


Naive solution: After every remove query, find the sum to remove and add new subset sums
by calculating it through iteration. O(N*N)

Optimal: If we track subset sum in one set and subset ranges in another set then for
every query we can find relevant subset by using binary search and update both
the segments as well as the sum values.
ex: nums = [1,2,5,6,1], removeQueries = [0,3,2,4,1]
current_segments = {0, 4}
remove = 0 new_segments = {1, 4} sums = {14}
remove = 3 new_segments = {1, 2} {4, 4} sums = {7, 1}
remove = 2 new_segments = {1, 1} {4, 4} sums = {2 ,1}

