# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
This problem can be solved with simple array traversal approach.
Take i as an opponent index, which should increment only when the player has strictly greater energy and experience than the opponent.
If the player does not satisfied any of these condition then it should train for hours equivalnet to the difference b/w energy or experience (whichever is unsatisfied) + 1 (+1 because of strictly condition). This training hour can be counted by any variable.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/ea84da01-69e8-43ed-a727-1e413665b43f_1695661187.3696287.png)


# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int minNumberOfHours(int energy, int experience, int[] Energy, int[] Experience) {

        int count = 0;
        int n = Energy.length;
        int i = 0;
        while(i < n){
            //when the player energy and experience are greater than that of opponent
            //let them fight and decrease the energy and increse the experience of the player
            if(energy > Energy[i] && experience > Experience[i]){
                experience += Experience[i];
                energy -= Energy[i];
                i++;
                continue;
            }
            //if energy of player is less than the energy of the opponent
            //train hours equivalent to the differnces b/w energy + 1
            if(energy <= Energy[i]){
                count += Energy[i] - energy + 1;
                energy += Energy[i] - energy + 1;
            }
            //conditions for experience is same as energy
            if(experience <= Experience[i]){
                count += Experience[i] - experience + 1;
                experience += Experience[i] - experience + 1;
            }
        }

        return count;
    }
}
```

