Variable Description and Usage:
1. ***occ*** = occurences of each digit from 0 to 9
2. ***z*** = first half of the palindromic string, it then becomes the 2nd half
3. ***x*** = new first half of the palindromic string
4. ***maxu*** = taking one max integer that can be in the middle of the palindromic string

Approach :
So the crux is that thw palindromic string will be greatest when we start with big digits and go in a decreasing order to the middle. The middle element has to be the highest one possible (I've stored it here in maxu). If there is no maxu, and there is a non used '0', we can put it in the middle of the palindromic string. This will increase the size of the string and hence the number.

Code : )
```
class Solution {
public:
    string largestPalindromic(string num) {
        int occ[10]={0};
        int n=num.size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
            occ[num[i]-'0']++;

        string z="";
        int maxu=INT_MIN;
        for(int i=9;i>=1;i--){
            if(occ[i]%2==1){
                maxu=max(maxu,i);
                occ[i]--;
            }
            if(occ[i]%2==0 && occ[i]>1){
                for(int j=1;j<=occ[i]/2;j++)
                    z+=to_string(i);
                occ[i]=0;
            }
        }
        if(z!=""){
            if(occ[0]>1)
                for(int j=1;j<=occ[0]/2;j++)
                    z+='0';
        }
        string x=z;
        reverse(z.begin(),z.end());
        if(maxu!=INT_MIN)
            x+=to_string(maxu);
        else if(occ[0]%2==1)
            x+='0';
        x+=z;
        if(num!="" && x=="")
            return "0";
        return x;
    }
};
```
Extra : )
* Save no. of occurances of each digit 
* Define a max for the middle of the palindrome
* Loop over the digits in a decreasing order
* Append even no. of occurances of a digit to our string z 
* Any digit who is greatest and has odd occ will be the maxu
* Copy z in x
* Reverse z
* Add maxu to x
* Add z to x
* For a string like "000000" just return 0
* Return x

