![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/6a108694-582d-4097-8f78-d503e8534327_1661421544.0533235.png)

**Explaination :**

Let's understand this question in an intuitive manner. For solving this question, let us note some points from question itself:

Palindromic Number:  In a palindromic number, content from mid to end is the mirror image of the content from starting to mid.
Example: XYZZYX , here element from index 3 to index 5 is mirror image of element from 0 to 2 so, we can say that it is a palindromic number.

*  Point 1 : In even size palindromic number , frequency of every digit is even. In odd size number, frequency of every digit is even except middle.

*  Point 2:   For largest number, number should start with largest available digit.
*  Point 3:  If we are able to create first half of the palindrome like XYZ then we can add it's mirror image to complete the palindrome like XYZ ZYX.

 Using these points, we will solve this problem.

Step 1:  Save the frequency of digit in given string.
step 2:  second, we are creating first half of the palindrome , by adding the largest digit first whose frequency is more than 1 and can be used even times.
step 3:  we are also saving largest digit whose frequency is odd, so that we can add it in the middle of palindrome.
step 4: If only zeroes are present then return single zero in the result.

```
class Solution {
public:
    string largestPalindromic(string num) {
        vector<int>hash(10);     // hash for storing frequency
        int size{};
        char ch = '#';
        string res="";
        for(auto i:num) hash[i-'0']++;   // increasing frequencies of digits.(step1)

        for(char i = '9'; i >= '0'; i--){      // traversing the digit from largest to smallest. (step2)

		// hash[i-'0']&1 check whether value is odd or not
            if(hash[i-'0']&1 && ch == '#') ch = i;   //  storing the largest odd digit in ch . (step3)

			// if there is no digit is present more than 0 zero and only zeroes digit is present
			// in num then there is no meaning to add multiple zeroes in result.
            if(i == '0' && res.size() == 0) continue; 

			// adding only half frequency of digit 
            size = hash[i-'0']/2;
            while(size--) res.push_back(i);
        }

        size = res.size()-1;
        if(ch != '#') res.push_back(ch);      // adding the odd character
        for(int i = size; i >=0; i--) res.push_back(res[i]);  // adding the mirror image of first half of palindrome
        if(res.size() == 0) return "0"; // if digit is forming valid palindrome or only zeroes was present in the string then return single zero.
        return res;
    }
};
```
**Time complexity : O(N)
Space complexity : O(1)**

