solutions.content:
A greedy approach is putting all numbers from 9 to 0 one after another. I'd like to consider serveral cases

* The length of the Palindromic is odd, it happens when there is a number where its frequency is odd. in this case we need to find the number that will be added into the middle of the final result.

* The length of Palindromic is even, it should be simple to solve, we just put need numbers into the final string in order. For instance, we have 2 of "9" and 4 of "8",... we will add into string like "98.....89"
* Zero at the beginning of the output. in this case, we need to return "0" in case there is no other number with frequency=0. if there are some numbers with a frequency greater than 0, return the biggest one. For instance, "9007800" -> return "9"

```
class Solution {
public:
    string largestPalindromic(string s) {
        int m[255] = {};
        string mid = "";
        int left = 0, right = s.size()-1;

        for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) m[s[i]]++;
        for (int c = '9'; c >= '0'; c--) {
            while(m[c] >= 2) {
                s[left++] = c;
                s[right--] = c;
                m[c] -=2;
            }
            if (mid == "" && m[c] == 1) mid = c;
        }
        if (s[0] == '0') {
            if (mid == "") return "0";
            else return mid;
        } 

        return s.substr(0, left) + mid + s.substr(right+1);
    }
};
```

