solutions.content:
**Step 1 :** Create a frequency array containing frequency of each integer of num.
**Step 2 :** Now our freq[] will only have either 0, 1 or more than 1.
a) If 0, no need to do anything.
b) If 1, we cant make a pair. But we can make a mid element (Discussed in Step 3).
c) If 2 or more, we can a pair. 
	**Eg -** 
		freq[i] = 6 --> we can make a pair of 6/2 = 3
		freq[i] = 7 --> we can make a pair of 7/2 = 3 and we can use remaining 1 to build a mid element (Step 2).
		**Note : Trim zeroes (if any).**

**Step 3 :** Now frequency of all elements will be either 0 or 1.
	Find the largest element in freq[] of freq 1. 
	Why largest? Because lets say left part is 44 and freq[] = {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 1}, then  44'9' > 44'7' 
	**Note : Mid can be only 1 element or no element.**

**Step 4 :** 
	Merge all of them.
	Eg : 	left part : 447
		mid part : 9
		right part : reverse(left part) = 744
		Required ans = 4479744

```
public String largestPalindromic(String num) {
    int[] freq = new int[10];
	for (char ch : num.toCharArray()) {       // create a frequency array
		int i = (int)(ch-'0');
		freq[i] += 1;
	}

	StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
	for (int i = 9; i >= 0; i--) {            // calculating first part
		if (freq[i] > 1) {
			int times = freq[i]/2;
			while (times > 0) {
				sb.append(i);
				times--;
			}
			freq[i] = freq[i]%2;
		}
	}

	trimZeros(sb);                         // trim zeros

	String mid = "";
	for (int i = 9; i >= 0; i--) {         //calculating mid
		if (freq[i] == 1) {       
			mid += i;
			break;
		}
	}

	String ans = "";                        // Merge all 
	ans += sb.toString();
	ans += mid;
	ans += sb.reverse().toString();
	return ans.isEmpty() ? "0" : ans;
}

void trimZeros(StringBuilder sb) {
	int zeroLength = 0;
	for (int i = 0; i < sb.length(); i++) {         // calculate the number of prefix zeros
		if (sb.charAt(i) != '0') {
			break;
		}
		else {
			zeroLength++;
		}
	}
	sb.delete(0, zeroLength);                      // delete those zeros
}
```

