solutions.content:
## Points to ponder:
**Point 1:** If a palindrome is of `even` length, all its characters have even frequency (e.g., `9229`)
**Point 2:** If a palindrome is of `odd` length, all its characters have even frequency except for the `middle` character (e.g., `92129`)

**Steps to follow:**
1. we count `frequency` of all chars.
1. we `build first half of the palindrome` by inserting bigger digits first ,i.e., starting with 9, then 8, then 7 and so on. (becasuse starting with the largest digit guarantees the largest value palindrome)
1. we also keep track of the biggest `middle` digit with odd frequency `if there exists any` (becasuse bigger middle digit makes bigger palindrome value)
1. we `remove leading zeros` from the first half of the palindrome.
1. `ans = first_half + middle + reversed_first_half`
1. if `size` of ans is `zero`, we return `"0"` (in this case, the input string contained only zeros)

**Complexity**
Time `O(n)`
Space `O(n)`

```
string largestPalindromic(string num) {
    int freq[10] = {0}; //from 0-9 there are 10 digits. We intitialize their count with zero.
    int middle = -1; //We will try to take the maximum digit with odd frequency for the middle as we are trying to build the largest palindrome possible
    for(char n: num) freq[n-'0']++; // subtracting '0' converts char to int
	/*************building the first half of palindrome(with leading zeros) and max middle digit with odd frequency***************/
    string half;
	for(int i=9; i>=0; i--){ //We wii try to build the largest palindrome possible. So we insert largest digit(9, 8, 7, ...) first
		int times = freq[i]/2;
		while(times--) half += i+'0';
		if(freq[i] & 1) middle = max(middle, i); //trying to keep track of the largest digit with odd frequency
	}
    /*************Removing leading zeros from first half of the palindrome***************/
    string zeroless; // for storing the string half without leading zeros
    int ind = -1;
    for(int i=0; i<half.size(); i++) if(half[i] != '0') {ind = i; break;} //ind keeps track of the first non-zero char
    if(ind != -1) { //if ind stays -1, it means input string contained only zeros
		for(int i=ind; i<half.size(); i++) zeroless+=half[i];
	} 
    /*************Building the palindrome***************/
    string ans;
	ans += zeroless; // inserting the first half of the palindrome
    if(middle != -1) {  //if middle stays -1, there was no digit with odd frequency. So there won't be a middle digit. Length of palindrome will be even.
		ans += middle+'0'; // adding '0' converts int to char
	}
    reverse(zeroless.begin(), zeroless.end()); 
    ans += zeroless; //inserting the reversed second half of the array 
    return ans.size()==0 ? "0" : ans; //If input string is full of zeros, answer is "0". As we stripped all leading zeros, we gotta handle it separately!
}
```
