1. First seperate of all digit in sting and store in a sorted Map(Treemap).
	```n = "444947137"```
	```{1=1, 3=3, 4=4444, 7=77, 9=9}```
2. Now we know that Palindrome can be made using even number of occurance of digits apart from the middle one.
```like  121 or 1221```
3. Now we traverse the map in sorted order 
	* Find the maximum digit with odd occurance to place in middle. ```maxOdd```
	* Make a half of palidrome using half of available digits. ```res```
4. Now result would be ``` res + maxODD + reverse(res)```
5. Check for edge cases.


```
class Solution {
    public String largestPalindromic(String num) {
        int n = num.length(); String res = ""; 
        boolean flag = false;
        Map<Character, String> tmap = new TreeMap<Character, String>();
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            String str = "";
            if(tmap.containsKey(num.charAt(i))){
                str = tmap.get(num.charAt(i));
            }
            str += num.charAt(i);
            tmap.put(num.charAt(i), str);
        }
        char maxOdd = ' ';
        for(Character key : tmap.keySet()) {
            String str = tmap.get(key);
            res = res + str.substring(0,str.length()/2);

            if(str.length() % 2 == 1)
                maxOdd = key;
        }
		// handle "00009" case
        if(!res.isEmpty() && res.charAt(res.length()-1) == '0')
            res = "";

        StringBuilder res1 = new StringBuilder(res);
        if(maxOdd != ' ')
            res = res1.reverse().toString() + maxOdd + res;
        else
            res = res1.reverse().toString() + res;

		// handle "00000" case
        return res.isEmpty() ? "0" : res;
    }
}
```

