# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
* Count digits in the input
* Construct the left part
    * Larger digits with the count > 1 go first
    * Skip 0 if the left part is empty
* Pick the middle digit
    * Largest digit with the odd count
    * Pick 0 only if the left part is empty
* Output left + [mid] + reverse(left)

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
impl Solution {
    pub fn largest_palindromic(num: String) -> String {
        let freq = num.bytes().fold([0; 10], |mut acc, b| { acc[(b - b'0') as usize] += 1; acc });

        let mut left = vec![];
        let mut mid = None;
        for (digit, freq) in freq.into_iter().enumerate().filter(|&(_, f)| *f > 0).rev() {
            if freq % 2 != 0 || (digit == 0 && left.is_empty()) { mid.get_or_insert(digit); }
            if digit == 0 && left.is_empty() { continue; }

            for _ in 0..(freq / 2) {
                left.push(b'0' + digit as u8);
            }
        }
        let mut right = left.iter().rev().cloned().collect::<Vec<_>>();
        if let Some(digit) = mid { left.push(b'0' + digit as u8); }
        left.append(&mut right);

        String::from_utf8(left).unwrap()
    }
}
