# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
* Important mathematical properties of the palindrome:
    1) It consists of even number of all digits, except that 1 can be there once.
    2) If we are talking about the max possible palindrome, the digits will be ordered from max to min first, then an odd one if exists, and then min to max
* Since we are repeatedly getting max and min numbers, use heap.
* Be careful to handle multiple edge cases related to zeros.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
* Store all even numbers in two heaps, one min and one max.
* We could potentially do it in one, and then fill the second part by reversing the first part. It would be more space efficient, but this is more readable to me.
* Fill heaps. 
* Get the max odd number.
* Finally compose the result: first by adding numbers from the max heap, then an odd number if exists, then from min heap.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
