# Intuition
Every second a node will infect all its neighbours. The next second, they will infect their neighbours. Hence we have to spread the virus in a breadth-fashion. So we have to consider the use of a simple BFS approach.

# Approach
To solve this question using a BFS approach, firstly we would need to convert the tree into a graph, as a node's child in a binary tree doesn't have a pointer to its parent. We need a two way connection here. Smart choice would be to convert the tree, into an adjacency list.
After doing that, simply do a BFS traversal. Key thing to note in these type of problems is that:-
- To get only the neighbours of the current node; before starting the traversal, take out the size of the queue. 
### The current size of the queue will represent the number of neighbouring nodes of that node.
- Rest is easy, then do your traditional BFS. See the code for better understanding.

# Complexity
- ## Time complexity:
The time complexity of the solution would be $$O(N)$$. As we are traversing the whole binary tree at max, twice.

- ## Space complexity:
Space complexity would also be $$O(N)$$. As we are using extra space in form of Queue and representing the tree as graph.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> adj[100005];
    void graph(TreeNode* root){
        if(!root or (root->left == NULL and root->right == NULL)){
            return;
        }
        if(root->left != NULL){
            adj[root->val].push_back(root->left->val);
            adj[root->left->val].push_back(root->val);
        }
        if(root->right != NULL){
            adj[root->val].push_back(root->right->val);
            adj[root->right->val].push_back(root->val);
        }
        graph(root->left);
        graph(root->right);
    }
    int amountOfTime(TreeNode* root, int start) {
        graph(root);
        vector<int> vis(100005, 0);
        queue<int> q;
        q.push(start);
        int ctr = -1;
        while(!q.empty()){
            int sz = q.size();
            while(sz--){
                int curr = q.front();
                q.pop();
                vis[curr] = true;
                for(auto i : adj[curr]){
                    if(!vis[i]){
                        q.push(i);
                    }
                }
            }
            ctr++;
        }
        return ctr;
    }
};
```

