# Intuition
The Main idea behind this question : 
Do a `BFS` from the node with the value of `start`. This is what we want to do.
The simplest thing that comes into my mind for doing this is first making an `adjacency list` storing all the neighbours of all the nodes ( take care of directionality). Because I am considering edges to be bidirectoinal I need to take care of this during the BFS implementation, which imho is no that hard, we just need a lookup table to check if a node has been visited or not .

Then it's just about execuing BFS. 
Below is the code using the above idea.

# Code
```
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode() {}
 *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
 *         this.val = val;
 *         this.left = left;
 *         this.right = right;
 *     }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    public int amountOfTime(TreeNode root, int start) {
        int t = 0;
        if(root == null)return 0;
        if(root.left == null && root.right == null)return 0;

        HashMap<Integer, ArrayList<Integer>>map = new HashMap<Integer, ArrayList<Integer>>();

        dfs(-1, root, map);
        ArrayList<Integer>adj = map.get(start);

        // now do a BFS.
        Queue<Integer>q = new LinkedList<>();
        q.offer(start);
        HashMap<Integer, Boolean>visited = new HashMap<Integer, Boolean>();
        while(!q.isEmpty()){
            int sz = q.size();
            while(sz-->0){
                int top = q.poll();
                if(visited.containsKey(top))continue;
                visited.put(top, true);
                ArrayList<Integer>it = map.get(top);
                if(it == null)continue;
                int size = it.size();
                for(int i = 0; i<size; ++i){
                    if(visited.containsKey(it.get(i)))continue;
                    q.offer(it.get(i));
                }
            }
            if(q.isEmpty() == true)return t;
            ++t;
        }
        return t;
    }

    public void dfs(int parent, TreeNode root, HashMap<Integer, ArrayList<Integer>>map){
        if(root == null)return;
        if(parent == -1){
            if(root.left != null){
                if(map.get(root.val) == null){
                    map.put(root.val, new ArrayList<Integer>());
                    ArrayList<Integer>arr = map.get(root.val);
                    arr.add(root.left.val);
                    map.put(root.val, arr);
                }else{
                    ArrayList<Integer>arr = map.get(root.val);
                    arr.add(root.left.val);
                    map.put(root.val, arr);
                }
            }
            if(root.right != null){
                 if(map.get(root.val) == null){
                    map.put(root.val, new ArrayList<Integer>());
                    ArrayList<Integer>arr = map.get(root.val);
                    arr.add(root.right.val);
                    map.put(root.val, arr);
                }else{
                    ArrayList<Integer>arr = map.get(root.val);
                    arr.add(root.right.val);
