solutions.content:
bottom-up recursion
use 'negative' integer to indicate we have met burn node

case 1: haven't met burn node 
=> pass height of tree to parent

case 2: current node is burn node 
=> change the signal to '-1'; start updating global max of burning time

case 3: have met burn node
=> pass the negative result to parent(indicate the burning time); update burning time if necessary

```
class Solution {
    int max = 0;
    public int amountOfTime(TreeNode root, int start) {
        helper(root, start);
        return max;
    }
    private int helper(TreeNode root, int start) {
        if (root == null) {
            return 0;
        }
        int left = helper(root.left, start);
        int right = helper(root.right, start);
        if (root.val == start) { //case 2
            max = Math.max(max, Math.max(left, right));
            return -1;
        } else if (left < 0 || right < 0) { //case 3
            max = Math.max(max, Math.abs(left) + Math.abs(right));
            return left < 0 ? left - 1 : right - 1;
        } else { //case 1
            return Math.max(left, right) + 1;
        }
    }
}
```

