solutions.content:
Basically we have to find the **max distance from the infected node to the leaf node.**

The intuition is that if the infected node is on the left subtree and distance between current node and the infected node on the left is **```k```**, then the max distance will be **```k + right_subtree_height```**. Same goes for the right side.

There will be four cases for the current node:

1.  **If the infected node is on the left side of current node and distance between them is k, then ```max_distance = k + right_subtree_height```**

1.  **If the infected node is on the right side of current node and distance is k, then ```max_distance = k + left_subtree_height```**

1. **If the current node is itself the infected node then ```max_distance = height(current_node)```**

1.   If current node is none of the above do nothing.

Finally we find max_distance for each node and update our ans.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/e6e387ae-c951-4ee2-8341-fe3371d8f542_1661107646.7277312.jpeg)



**C++ code:**

```
class Solution {
public:
    int amountOfTime(TreeNode* root, int start) {
        int ans = 0;
        int temp = solve(root, start, ans);
        return ans;
    }

    int solve(TreeNode* root, int start, int &ans) {  // returns the distance of infected node from the current node, returns -1 if infected node is not found
        if(root == NULL) return -1;

        if(root->val == start) {                    // case 3: if current node is infected node, find height
            ans = max(ans, height(root)-1);         // updates the ans
            return 1;
        }

        int k_left = solve(root->left, start, ans);
        if(k_left != -1) {                          // case 1: if infected node is on the left
            ans = max(ans, height(root->right) + k_left);   // updates the ans
            return k_left+1;
        }

        int k_right = solve(root->right, start, ans);
        if(k_right != -1) {                         // case 2: if infected node is on the right
            ans = max(ans, height(root->left) + k_right);   // updates the ans
            return k_right + 1;
        }

        return -1;                                  // case 4: do nothing

    }

    int height(TreeNode* root) {
        if(root == NULL) return 0;
        return max(height(root->left), height(root->right)) + 1;
    }
};
