Solution 1: Trivial but straightforward, go tree traversal and build a graph based on current node's parent node, left node and right node. Then start either dfs or bfs the graph from the start node, return the longest path.

Solution 2: beats 100%, two dfs
First dfs, traverse the tree and record all nodes' left height and right height, you can use a map to record the heights.
Second dfs, traverse the tree and **find the start node**, and we know that the **ans = max of (upper distance from parent, left height, right height)**. The key here is how to calculate the **upper distance**?
--> A **left child's upper distance** is either its **parent's right height** or its parent's upper distance
--> A **right child's upper distance** is either its **parent's left height** or its parent's upper distance.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/7101a394-6b96-4a8e-9530-5ca4f1102519_1661057580.1047556.png)
```
// SOLUTION 1: BUILD THE GRAPH AND RUN BFS/DFS
class Solution {
    Map<Integer, List<Integer>> map = new HashMap();
    Set<Integer> visited = new HashSet();
    public int amountOfTime(TreeNode root, int st) {
        dfs(root, -1);
        Queue<Integer> q = new LinkedList();
        q.offer(st);
        visited.add(st);
        int ans = 0;
        while (!q.isEmpty()) {
            int size = q.size();
            boolean ok = false;
            for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
                int cur = q.poll();
                for (int next : map.get(cur)) {
                    if (visited.contains(next)) continue;
                    visited.add(next);
                    q.offer(next);
                    ok = true;
                }
            }
            if (ok) ans++;
        }
        return ans;
    }

    public void dfs(TreeNode node, int p) {
        map.put(node.val, new ArrayList());
        if (p != -1) map.get(node.val).add(p);
        if (node.left != null) {
            map.get(node.val).add(node.left.val);
            dfs(node.left, node.val);
        }
        if (node.right != null) {
            map.get(node.val).add(node.right.val);
            dfs(node.right, node.val);
        }
    }
}
